          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>4983</commentid>
            <who name="Derrell Lipman">derrell.lipman</who>
            <bug_when>2008-09-02 14:18:14 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>The two are related (both apply to the row focus indicator), but are different issues.  #1216 is to disable the row focus indicator entirely.  Virtual trees, for example, typically don&#39;t need or want a row focus indicator.  

#1217, this bug, is for when the row focus indicator is in use, but to allow making that row focus indicator go away at programmer control or automatically when the mouse leaves the table.
</thetext>
